The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, April 14, 2004 				 Eight killed in Chechen clash
																								Moscow, April 13 (Reuters): Separatist guerrillas killed eight members of Chechnyas pro-Moscow police force in a bloody 24 hours for the turbulent Russian region, local officials said today.																								Officials said the police came under rebel fire as they drove into a village in the low-lying Gudermes district east of Grozny.																								Yesterday evening a group of rebels opened fire on the police as they came in. Eight were killed and one injured, local administration head Vakha Magamgaziyev said. The killed were seven interior ministry officials and a police inspector, who was killed when they searched the village of Ishkhoy-Yurt for police and state officials.
